reviews.text: We went on a Thursday after 7 and it was 198 +10%. It's good meat and a clean and relatively quiet place. There are lot's of people there but everyone was respectful. The dessert selection is great.

First time for us to this restaurant. It was a good experience. Our group of 9 went from 5:30-7:00pm on a weeknight. If you finish before 7pm (weeknight), the price is HK$128 plus 10% service charge for the all 
-you-can-eat Korean BBQ meal. There was a decent range of food including raw meat and veggies for BBQ cooking, cooked food, drinks, sushi, soup and desserts. Service was good. We had to pay with cash. It was my first time to use a rectangular cooking surface and there was wax paper to cook on. It worked well. Also there was a mini space on the edges of the cooking surface that had some soup broth. You could cook some veggies and mushrooms in it. Overall a very decent Korean BBQ restaurant. I will be going back soon.
Lunch buffet serves hot meat and desserts with much varieties. Very good place for lunch.

nice Korean BBQ. 
cutie doggy pudding
Perfect

reviews.text: 元朗及旺角店都係一樣咁差👎🏼
超正👍😋
午市幾十至百幾，晚市二百幾，爐細燒好耐，叫埋海鮮餐更加冇時間，火鍋另加錢，有熟食魚生甜品雪糕，可以玩下綿花糖機班戟機
我想講！若然成本过高！不如加多20，免燒的選擇真的縮得过多！😀
返學晏晝成日同同學去食，D野食一般般，但夠平同埋係自助餐！！
